    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-10-30T16:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-10-30T16:00:00-05:00" n="196"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d196">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72112/10610</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in France</hi> (<persName
                        corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_SWG1" type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Sharp</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Paris</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-10-30T21:00:00+00:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">October 30, 1918, 9 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received October 31, 2.41 p.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>5638. War Trade Board, Bureau of Enemy Trade [from <persName
                        corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_MG1">McFadden</persName>]:</p>
                <p>No. 549. At the meeting of the trade license conference, the following resolution
                    was adopted, subject to the approval of the Associated <pb facs="0239" n="1073"
                        xml:id="pg_1073"/> Governments, for the purpose of (1) avoiding delay in
                    decisions of the various conferences becoming effective, and (2) giving the
                    various Associated Governments a fixed time in which to register an objection to
                    such decisions: <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>In order to avoid delay in the execution of the decisions taken by the
                            Inter-Allied Trade License Conferences at Paris, London, and Washington,
                            it is resolved that decision of the said conference shall become binding
                            upon the various governments whose representatives participate therein,
                            after a lapse of ten days from the date of the meeting at which such
                            decision is taken unless objections are registered by one of the
                            Governments before the period of ten days [has] passed.</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <p>Please instruct if you agree. Please advise <persName>Frothingham</persName> to
                    whom we are sending copy of this telegram. <persName
                        corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_MG1">McFadden</persName>.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_SWG1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Sharp</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
